      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LE CARDINAL (3) has produced three nice efforts since kicking off his campaign with back-to-back wins, beaten only 1.4m into second here last week. Was behind race rival MOST EXCITING when third here prior but draws better than that rival this time so could turn the tables. The wide barrier may not be in favour of MOST EXCITING (7) but his form is hard to knock, beaten narrowly into second after racing parked in both outings since kicking off his campaign with back-to-back wins. He may be capable enough to overcome the draw. ROYAL APPOINTMENT (1) has been coming from wider of second row draws of late and hasn't been too far away so can be competitive from the inside barrier. LEAVEMEOUT (5) draws wider but is worth including after finishing runner-up in his last two appearances.",
